The most recent report of the 'Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission' (Florida Commission for the Conservation of Fish and Fauna) shows a general decline in concentrations of Red glow in parts of Tampa Bay Area (on the west coast of Florida in the USA).
According to the committee, it is reported on a fragmented increase in the red glow in the provinces of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier, which could indicate a decrease in concentrations.
The Red glow extends over an average of 200 km of coastline, from northern Pinellas to southern Lee counties.
There are about 16 km off the coast of Hillsborough County spots, but in less places than last week.
Red glow was also seen in Pasco County.
Medium-sized concentrations have been reported off the coast of Pinellas County last week, low to high concentrations off the coast of Hillsborough County, background to high concentrations in Manatee County, background to high concentrations at or off the coast of Sarasota County, background to high concentrations in Charlotte County, background to high concentrations at or off the coast of Lee County, and low concentrations in Collier County.
It is reported that airways are irritated in the provinces of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee, and Collier.
In the northwest of Florida, there has been no mention of respiratory irritation in the past week.
